# Test conventions

## Headless Chrome

Always run Maven with `GITHUB_ACTIONS=true` so `WebTestExtension` matches CI headless mode — see [test-headless-github-actions.mdc](test-headless-github-actions.mdc).

## Annotations

- `@WebTest` on browser tests (Quarkus + Selenium via `WebTestExtension`); tagged `web`.
- `@QuarkusIntegrationTest` for HTTP/DB integration tests without a browser; tagged `quarkus`.
- `@UnitTest` on plain JUnit tests with no Quarkus boot; tagged `unit`.
- `mvn clean test` runs all tags; `mvn test -Ptest-unit|test-quarkus|test-web` runs one tag (CI runs these in parallel).

## App DSL

- Inject `App app` in test methods; chain navigation (`app.access().loginModal()...`).
- Add new page objects as inner classes on `App`, not raw `WebDriver` in tests.

## Given builders

- `Given.user()`, `Given.post()`, `Given.blog()`, `Given.customPage()`.
- `Given.cleanup()` when tests create data that could affect others (shared DB).
- `Given.randomCover()` / `Given.randomImage()` for upload flows.
- `Given.transaction(...)` for custom persistence in builders.

## URLs in tests

- Use relative paths matching production routes; prefer `@TestHTTPResource` for base URL when needed.

## Time

- Do **not** call the system clock in tests: no `LocalDateTime.now()`, `YearMonth.now()`, `Instant.now()`, `System.currentTimeMillis()`, `Clock.systemDefaultZone()`, or `new Date()`.
- Use fixed constants from [`TestTimes`](../../src/test/java/dev/vepo/contraponto/shared/TestTimes.java) (`REFERENCE`, `REFERENCE_MONTH`, `REFERENCE_DATE`, `FAR_FUTURE`) or an explicit `LocalDateTime.of` / `YearMonth.of` when a different instant is required.
- Dashboard and other UI tests that depend on “current month” in production must open analytics (or seed data) with explicit `year` / `month` query params — do not rely on the JVM clock matching seeded timestamps.
